race.comment: QUICK AS SILVER (2) scored by 1L at Toodyay last start to shed his maiden tag and did so with a solid figure. The wide draw today is a niggle, though the 3kg claim comes in handy from Riordan and if he gets the luck he needs in running, he can bring up back-to-back wins. NATIVE FLOWER (5) couldn't hold on at Toodyay when favourite and leading throughout over 1100m. She'll be better for that run however and she should be nearing her top now. Maps to be prominent once again and she can make every post a winner this time. TROPICAL SUN (1) has been getting well back from tricky barrier, but got the job done last start at Toodyay in a photo finish. The inside draw may see her sit a touch closer this time, but the firm deck suits and she can go back-to-back. SOLAR SYSTEM (4) looks well placed coming back to this grade and is not to be discounted. HELLAINE (9) can improve under this scenario and is not to be discounted.
